  <h1>
    Phosphorus-doped Wafer
  </h1>
  <h3>
   Source
  </h3>
  <text><style color="0xaaaaaa" italic="true">Note: this page is ported from MCMOD's GTCEu wiki.<br/>Author: <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://center.mcmod.cn/179043/">花海</style>, <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://github.com/Yefancy">KilaBash</style><br/></style></text>
  <text>
    Phosphorus-doped Wafer, an intermediate wafer material.
  </text> 
  <br/>
  <h3>Source</h3>
  <text>
    Phosphorus-doped Wafers are produced by cutting <style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:circuits/silicon_boule" hover-info="click link">Phosphorus-doped Monocrystalline Silicon Boule</style> in an at lowest HV-Tier voltage <style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:machines/cutter" hover-info="click link">cutter</style>.
    <br/>
    (<style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:multiblock/cleanroom" hover-info="click link">Cleanroom</style> is required)
  </text>
  <recipe id="gtceu:cutter/cut_phosphorus_boule_water"/>
  <br/>
  <h3>Usage</h3>
  <text left-margin="10">
    - 8 EU/t <style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:covers/solar_panel_ulv" hover-info="click link">ULV Solar Panel</style>;
  </text>
  <recipe id="gtceu:shaped/solar_panel_basic"/>
  <br/>
  <text left-margin="10">
    - Phosphorus-doped wafers can be used to produce wafers instead of <style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:circuits/silicon_wafer" hover-info="click link">silicon wafers</style> in a <style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:machines/laser_engraver" hover-info="click link">Laser Engraver</style>, which can increase the yield up to <style color="0xff5555">4 times</style>.
    <br/>
    <br/>
    - Phosphorus-doped wafers has unique recipes:
  </text>
  <recipe id="gtceu:laser_engraver/engrave_soc_phosphorus"/>
  <recipe id="gtceu:laser_engraver/engrave_pic_phosphorus"/>
  <recipe id="gtceu:laser_engraver/engrave_nor_phosphorus"/>
  <recipe id="gtceu:laser_engraver/engrave_nand_phosphorus"/>
